The Independent Corrupt Practices and other Related offences Commission (ICPC) says it will track 48 constituency and executive projects in Kaduna State. The commission said the projects were awarded from 2015-2019 worth N4,566,826,806.095 Addressing journalists at a news briefing on the commencement of the‎ second phase of the tracking exercise in the state, ICPC State Commissioner, Shehu Yahaya, said the projects to be tracked were in the rural areas. Shehu said the projects’ tracking would be done in collaboration with the Nigerian Institute of Quantity Surveyors (NIQS), civil society organisations (CSOs), Accountant General of the Federation, Bureau of Public Procurement (BPP) and other stakeholders. Dear our valued reader, we would like to hear your view about a membership club that we plan to launch. Kindly help us fill this survey. He said the exercise was expected to end in four weeks. ICPC to track 48 constituency projects worth over N4bn in Kaduna Constituency projects: ICPC to prosecute politicians, contractors who divert funds ICPC partners NOA on Constituency projects monitoring in Kaduna